column5: I'm heading there this morning. If anyone is there and would like to meet up for a coffee or what not, shoot me a PM for my number.
Busy Busy . Let us know if you come home with anything.

Good luck and I hope u find what your after but be careful on prices. Lived 3 miles from there for 18 years and frequented the auction countless times.  For the purchase of our 2 sleds and 2 atvs in each and every case we walked away from the auction without buying and on the 4 sepeate purchases got a better product for much less money on kijiji.  The purchases took us from Carp to Callender but well worth it.  Too many people bidding on too few items.

Filled with vehicles no one can sell or wants to. From my experiences anyway. Easy to get caught up in the bidding too! Lol. Not sure why I wanted a '92 Land Rover with 329000kms on it, but I rode all the way to $3500 until I finally came to my senses.  Good luck OP an keep us posted
Got a 2003 dodge sx2.0 5 speed with 125k for $900.00
That sounds like a good deal!,much work to be done?.
Not a thing. Got the safety and etest done today.
Anyone wanna buy the civic in the background?
